## Concerns

| Severity | ID | Issue |
|----------|-----|-------|
| **HIGH** | **33-01-T1 / 33-04** | `x64-platform.props` hardcodes `_DEBUG` / `DEBUG_LEVEL=2` with `Condition="'$(Platform)'=='x64'"` only — **no Debug vs Release split**. Release\|x64 projects importing it would compile with `_DEBUG`. Plans add Release\|x64 everywhere (04, 05) but validate mostly on Debug. |
| **HIGH** | **33-04 depends_on** | Plan 04 depends **only on 33-01**, not 33-03. Wave 3 can start after foundations while D3DX still in plugin source. Safer edge: 04-T3 adds sln x64 mappings for plugins **before** 05 adds plugin vcxproj x64 blocks — premature `msbuild … /p:Platform=x64 /t:Direct3d9` fails confusingly. |
| **HIGH** | **33-03-T1 / Pitfall 1** | `:4031` `D3DXMatrixMultiplyTranspose` is inside `#ifdef FFP` within `#ifdef VSPS` (`Direct3d9.cpp:4014-4036`). **gl05** = FFP+VSPS (uses transpose path); **gl07** = VSPS-only (else branch, **different multiply order**, no transpose); **gl06** = FFP-only (**entire VSPS block excluded**). Plan 03 A/B is **gl05/Tatooine-only** — can miss gl06/gl07 matrix regressions required by X64-02 (rasterMajor 6/7). |
| **HIGH** | **33-05-T1** | “163 AIL_* call sites” stub is **high blast-radius**. Miss one `AIL_*` → x64 link unresolved despite `/FORCE` grep gate. Plan acceptance (“grep `_M_X64` >= 1”) is **too weak** vs “zero `AIL_*` in x64 TU”. |
| **MEDIUM** | **33-RESEARCH / 33-03-T2** | **`D3DXLoadSurfaceFromSurface` count wrong: 4 live sites, not 8.** Verified: `Direct3d9_RenderTarget.cpp:317` + `Direct3d9_TextureData.cpp:549,603,681`. Plans over-scope Task 2 and under-specify per-site format checks (A3). |
| **MEDIUM** | **33-01-T3** | **tinyxml OutDir/import paths likely wrong depth.** Plan uses `..\..\..\..\..\compile\...` (5 levels) from `tinyxml/build/win32/`; peer `udplibrary.vcxproj` uses 4 levels from `library/udplibrary/`; `dpvs.vcxproj` uses 6 from `msvc8/`. Expect compile output in wrong place. |
| **MEDIUM** | **33-01 / 33-05** | SwgClient links `tinyxmld.lib;tinyxmld_STL.lib` (`SwgClient.vcxproj:103`). Plan 01 outputs `tinyxml.lib`. **Plan 05 never maps x64 tinyxml link name** — first x64 link likely LNK2019 unless 05 adds explicit swap. |
| **MEDIUM** | **33-02-T3 / census** | 32-01 probed **6/96** asm shaders byte-identical. Plan 02-T3 Tatooine smoke is necessary but **not sufficient** for “no silent null VS” on full corpus — acceptable if documented as sampling risk. |
| **MEDIUM** | **33-03-T3 / A4** | `optimizeIndexBuffer` no-op (`Direct3d9.cpp:4617+`) is reasonable but **NvTriStrip is already in SwgClient link** (`NvTriStrip.lib` in `:103`) — plan skips existing in-repo tool without noting it. Low correctness risk; perf regression unmeasured. |
| **MEDIUM** | **33-06-T1** | **dpvs.dll staging:** dpvs is `DynamicLibrary` (`dpvs.vcxproj`); no postbuild-to-stage today. Checklist includes `dpvs.dll` but Plan 05 postbuild only covers exe/plugins — **manual staging step easy to miss** before first boot. |
| **MEDIUM** | **ROADMAP vs handoff** | `ROADMAP.md` shows 32-02..32-05 unchecked; handoff + code show **32-02 COMPLETE**. Executors may hesitate on Plan 02’s “32-02 precondition” — **artifact drift only**, not a code blocker. |
